1 unit Oven-Ready Aluminum Trays
5 teaspoon (tsp) White Wine Vinegar
4 ounce Coleslaw Mix
4 tablespoon BBQ Sauce
2 tablespoon Mayonnaise
10 ounce Seasoned Precooked Potato Slices
½ cup Cheddar Cheese
10 ounce Chicken Cutlets
Salt
Pepper
Sugar
Cooking Oil

• Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to
425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.
• Pat chicken* dry with paper towels and season all over
with salt and pepper.
• Place chicken on one side of oven-ready tray (for
4 servings, place all the chicken in one tray). Top chicken
with BBQ sauce.

• Open package of potatoes and drain off any excess liquid.
• Place potatoes in a medium microwave-safe bowl,
separating any pieces that are stuck together. Cover with
plastic wrap; poke a few holes in wrap and microwave for
3 minutes. Toss with a drizzle of oil and a pinch of salt.
• Transfer seasoned potatoes to opposite side of tray from
chicken (for 4 servings, transfer potatoes to a second
tray). Top potatoes with cheddar. Bake on middle
rack (be sure your oven has preheated!) until chicken
is cooked through and potatoes are browned,
25-30 minutes. (For 4, bake two trays side by side on
middle rack.)

• Meanwhile, wash and dry bowl used for potatoes.
• In same bowl, combine coleslaw mix, mayonnaise, half
the vinegar, 1⁄2 tsp sugar, salt, and pepper (all the
vinegar and 1 tsp sugar for 4 servings). Refrigerate until
ready to serve.

• Divide BBQ chicken, cheddar potatoes, and coleslaw
between plates in separate sections. Serve.

***Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.***